Wing: Infuscated, darker around cross-vein r-m (
Fig. 60
).

Male: Differs from the female in the following ways: body 8.2 mm; wing 8.0 mm; facial tubercle matte; face totally yellowish-brown. Legs with longer bristles. Abdomen: Sternite 5 approximately rectangular, with rounded sides, posterior margin with v-shaped inverted invagination in the mid region, lateral bristles longer than bristles of mid region (
Fig. 22
). Terminalia: cerci fused in basal 2 / 3 , with long bristles on the sides and apex (
Figs. 23, 24
). Surstylus as long as cerci, narrowest medially, inner margins parallel, curved with apex clavate (
Fig. 25
). Parameres bilobed, with distal region curved (
Figs. 26, 27
). Aedeagus with a sclerotized stripe on basal half and middle (
Figs. 27, 28
). Epiphallus anchor-shaped with short branches and truncated apex (
Figs. 27, 28
).
